# Commit And Push Workflow

- Use Conventional Commits format: `type(scope): short summary`.
- Preferred types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`.
- Keep commit titles concise and imperative; include a brief body when rationale is non-obvious.
- Before committing, verify changes with `git status`, `git diff`, and relevant lint/type/test checks.
- Do not commit or push automatically unless the user explicitly asks.
- Prefer PR-first shipping; follow `.cursor/rules/pr-workflow.mdc` as the default release path.
- After any PR merge, reset branch context before new work:
  - switch to `main`
  - pull latest `origin/main`
  - create a new feature branch
- Do not reuse a merged branch, especially when remote auto-deletes merged branches.
- If the user explicitly requests direct push (for example, "commit and push to main"), allow bypassing PR.
- Never use force push unless explicitly requested by the user.
